''AKA IP Helper''

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dynamic_Host_Configuration_Protocol#Relay_agent_information_sub-options

https://www.arubanetworks.com/techdocs/AOS-CX/10.09/HTML/ip_services_4100i-6000-6100/Content/Chp_DHCP/dhc-rel-age.htm

A [[DHCP Relay Agent]] forwards [[DHCP|Dynamic Host Discovery Protocol]] messages to subnets that don't have a DHCP server in them.

This functionality is most commonly implemented in [[Routers|Router]] and [[Layer 3 Switches|Layer 3 Switch]].